  <diagram id="LHXHFopr-mRD5vGDSLDk" name="Descriptions">
    <mxGraphModel dx="1234" dy="833" grid="1" gridSize="10" guides="1" tooltips="1" connect="1" arrows="1" fold="1" page="1" pageScale="1" pageWidth="827" pageHeight="1169" math="0" shadow="0">
      <root>
        <mxCell id="0" />
        <mxCell id="1" parent="0" />
        <mxCell id="TeerpzXY_BvwL2jRelHO-2" value="&lt;h1 style=&quot;margin-top: 0px;&quot;&gt;Potions&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;Potions have arbitrary colors every game sessions. A potion color is bind to an effect of the potion. The description of a potion can describe known and unknown potion. The description of an unknown potion includes only its color (and also weight). The description of a known potion describes the effect of the potion.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;A potion becomes known when at least one potion with same effect was drunk.&lt;/p&gt;" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;overflow=hidden;rounded=0;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontSize=12;fontColor=default;labelBackgroundColor=default;" parent="1" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="40" y="40" width="680" height="180" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="TeerpzXY_BvwL2jRelHO-3" value="&lt;h1 style=&quot;margin-top: 0px;&quot;&gt;Weapon/Armor&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;;&quot; class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;font&gt;Every weapon or armor has base known characteristics, such as weight, effects(!), radius of light and others. But also, a weapon/armor can&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: light-dark(#ffffff, var(--ge-dark-color, #121212)); color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;be broken or improved (&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: light-dark(#ffffff, var(--ge-dark-color, #121212)); color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;have some modification), that can affect its characteristics.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;; min-height: 17px;&quot; class=&quot;p2&quot;&gt;&lt;font&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;;&quot; class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;font&gt;Only description of the known weapon should show the actual characteristics. For an unknown weapon only base numbers should be shown, plus remark that &quot;weapon(armor) looks unusual&quot; and can be broken or improved.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;; min-height: 17px;&quot; class=&quot;p2&quot;&gt;&lt;font&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;;&quot; class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;font&gt;A particular weapon entity can be known. To become known, a weapon should be used for some time.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;; min-height: 17px;&quot; class=&quot;p2&quot;&gt;&lt;font&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;;&quot; class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;font&gt;When some weapon or armor has been equipped first time a counter of turns is added to the Journal. That counter will be reduced every Turn. When the counter becomes 0, the weapon/armor have been marked as known.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;overflow=hidden;rounded=0;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontSize=12;fontColor=default;labelBackgroundColor=default;" parent="1" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="40" y="480" width="680" height="270" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="TeerpzXY_BvwL2jRelHO-4" value="&lt;h1 style=&quot;margin-top: 0px;&quot;&gt;Enemies&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;Enemies have a different damage, a different speed, a different behaviour, and can be in a different state.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;A player starts with no knowledge about enemies. A description of an enemy of an unknown class should not include nor a damage, nor a state of the enemy, nor an inside about its behaviour.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;A speed for a known enemy should be shown as a description, not a number:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&quot;Too slow&quot; &amp;gt;= +10&lt;br&gt;&quot;Slow&quot;&amp;nbsp; == [+5, +10)&lt;br&gt;&quot;Not so fast&quot; == [N, +5)&lt;br&gt;&quot;Fast&quot; == (-5, N)&lt;br&gt;&quot;Very fast&quot; &amp;lt;= -5&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;p&gt;A class of enemies become known&amp;nbsp; after killing at least one enemy of this class.&lt;/p&gt;" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;overflow=hidden;rounded=0;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontSize=12;fontColor=default;labelBackgroundColor=default;" parent="1" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="40" y="200" width="670" height="260" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
